                      <span>0</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2005-04-06</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This book is an absolute treat! It is well written, well structured, and very complete. It does expain what happens in the difficult conversations that each of us will experience once in a while.
<br />What I like best is that the book seems to be based upon the principes of Argyris, his ladder of inference and his Model I/Model II behaviour, and that they succeed to do it in a way that you can easily understand.
<br />What I don't understand, and this is the only issue I have with this book, is that I have not found any reference to the underlying theories. This makes the book very readable, but a short index of authors of the theories used by the authors should have been included.
<br />This book makes a great pair with 'The TAO of conversation' from Michael Kahn.
<br /></span>
                  
